The Internet of Things (IoT) security market is segmented based on various factors to provide a comprehensive view of the industry landscape. The segmentation by component includes hardware such as sensors and RFID tags, software including security and management solutions, and services encompassing professional and managed services. Each of these components plays a crucial role in addressing the security challenges posed by the interconnected nature of IoT devices. On the other hand, the segmentation by security type categorizes IoT security into network security, endpoint security, application security, and cloud security. These different types of security measures are essential to protect IoT networks from cyber threats and vulnerabilities. Furthermore, the vertical segmentation highlights key industry sectors like manufacturing, retail, healthcare, energy and utilities, and transportation that are driving the adoption of IoT security solutions to safeguard their operations and data.

